# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Table 3: asyncio.open_connection and asyncio.start_server __name__ identity
#
# asyncio.open_connection.__name__ == 'open_connection' (len=15)
# asyncio.start_server.__name__ == 'start_server' (len=12; same as StreamReader)
#
# open_connection is a coroutine that opens a network connection and returns
# (StreamReader, StreamWriter). start_server creates a TCP server and returns
# a Server object. NAME LENGTHS: start_server=12 < open_connection=15.
# New to extra179.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

